4,Dynamic Body Pilates,"80 Fifth Ave, Ste 1003, New York, NY 10011",(917) 613-1552,NULL,dynamicbodypilates.com,"Mon 7:00 am - 10:00 pm

Sun 10:00 am - 6:30 pm","We provide one-on-one customized Pilates to help people rediscover fitness, mobility, and ease.We train people with a variety of physical concerns and goals (regardless of degree) including people with:-pain and injury issues-neuromuscular challenges-weight issues-aging athletes-individuals for whom movement is a centerpiece of living a fulfilling life.The one thing all of our clients have in common is their desire to optimize their movement -- for life.Dynamic Body Pilates also goes beyond trauma, injury, and pain to fine-tune our clients' bodies so that they can prevent future issues. For all of our clients, Dynamic Body Pilates works to discover your body's innate capabilities -- enhancing and unleashing its full range of potential.We look forward to seeing you at our fully equipped Pilates studio in Union Square or in your NYC-based home or office!

Dynamic Body Pilates was developed for those who want--or need--to equip their body for life. Unlike with mainstream Pilates, we create a personalized, intelligent program just for you. Rather than restricting you to a set series of generic Pilates exercises, we draw from dozens of disciplines--including and beyond Pilates--to custom design your program to accommodate exactly what you need and want your body to do. Dynamic Body Pilates maximizes your specific flexibility, strength, coordination, and agility--while supporting these changes (and protecting you) with expert guidance in posture and alignment. As a result, your body transcends to the next level--regardless of your fitness or conditioning.Whether that means  making it easier to climb stairs or to walk, or becoming a stronger tennis player, we take Pilates principles, and more--and apply them uniquely to you, your lifestyle, and your life.  Dynamic Body Pilates: Your Body. Your Life",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/HffeMsZMdbCGEbYQJeEbtA/l.jpg,24

10,SwimJim Swimming Lessons - Midtown West,"725 10th Ave, Skyline Hotel, New York, NY 10019",(212) 749-7335,NULL,swimjim.com,"Mon Closed

Sun 9:00 am - 12:00 pm","SwimJim, Inc.'s teaching methodology is a safe, thoughtful, ordered approach to swimming, cultivating proficiency in a number of strokes. We believe the success with which our current and past students navigate the water proves our program's effectiveness.The most important aspect of our teaching process is our disciplined but loving dedication to getting children in and comfortable with the water. We are thoughtful and observant of student's behavioral and developmental patterns, and will never scare or intimidate a student. We will respond to their fears and concerns with love, humor and discipline, while guiding them through the necessary steps to become independent, competent swimmers.We deeply enjoy helping with children with special needs and development issues.  They are some of our favorite and best students!  The aquatic environment can provide them with a unique athletic experience other sports cannot.This firm, loving approach is the hallmark of SwimJim.

SwimJim was started in one location with 4 team members and 60 clients.  We only had lessons one day a week. Since that time SwimJim has expanded to multiple locations around New York City and has opened in the Hamptons and Houston Texas. The school now operates 7 days a week and 50 weeks out of the year. During that time of growth we created the Underwater Schoolhouse Teaching methodology added elite level swimmer and Olympic Gold Medalist Catherine Fox to the educational development team.  Together Jim and Catherine have developed a program that is world renowned and they have lectured and done clinics around the world. Their focus is on educating the whole person by addressing the emotional needs as well as the physical needs of the student. As SwimJim Continues to expand and grow, the entire team is focused on learning and discovering new ways to grow, educate and teach all people how to be safer in, on and around the water and enjoy the magic of swimming",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/6lh4V5Fj-WpqZVBfPO_ohA/l.jpg,1

column1: Asphalt Green is a non-profit sports and fitness organization in New York City that was founded by Dr. George E. Murphy, a professor of pathology at the Cornell University Medical College, and his wife, Annette. In 1972, the Murphy's, along with local residents, formed a charitable organization to renovate the Municipal Asphalt Plant and create Asphalt Green, a community center that offers sports activities. Asphalt Green officially opened in 1984 on the site of the former Municipal Asphalt Plant. The interior of plant was rehabilitated to house a gymnasium and multi-purpose classrooms.  In 1985, the outdoor turf sports field was added and in 1993, the AquaCenter was built next door, including a 50-meter Olympic pool and a 15,000 square-foot Fitness Center. In 2013, Asphalt Green opened a second location in lower Manhattan in Battery Park City. The Battery Park City campus includes a pool, fitness center, gymnasium, outdoor field and more",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/yioKSbBj6Tc-CKXH3f8D9w/l.jpg,41

22,MoshFit,"538 E 14th St, New York, NY 10009",(646) 263-9128,NULL,punkrope.com/moshfit,,"MoshFit is the brainchild of Punk Rope founder, Tim Haft, who believes that working out should be fun and what could be more fun that exercising in the back room of Otto's Shrunken Head, New York City's coolest tiki bar? During the 60-minute class you'll rock out while you work out as Haft, who is also a rock 'n' roll DJ provides a killer playlist that changes each week. You'll improve your cardio, strength, agility, and flexibility, while burning a ton of calories. And don't worry, the workout is perfectly safe. Save your stage diving and slam dancing for actual punk shows.MoshFit is appropriate for exercisers of all fitness levels. You'll work at your own pace and if a movement doesn't feel right we'll offer you a safe alternative. Space is limited to ensure you receive plenty of individual attention.Since we're all about staying hydrated and building community, class is followed by a special happy hour: all drafts and well drinks are only $4 for MoshFitters between 7:30pm and 8:30pm.

MoshFit was inspired by Punk Rope, which Tim Haft launched in 2004. Punk Rope is now the most popular rope-jumping based fitness class in the world, but Tim realized long ago that not everybody likes to jump rope. He wanted to create a fitness class with the same playful spirit and high energy as Punk Rope, but minus the rope jumping. Tim also wanted to offer a class that could be taught in a wide variety of settings not just gyms. Since MoshFit requires no equipment it can be offered virtually anywhere including the back room of a tiki bar",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/4690yE6WwCMvAf0X8Byn8A/l.jpg,6

Sun 12:00 pm - 7:30 pm","Djoniba Dance Centre, facebkdjonibacentre, is a pioneer in providing a great fitness alternative to gyms, for working out, losing weight and having fun. Heart-pumping ninety-minute classes combine stretching, strengthening and sculpting warm-ups followed by exciting ethnic/African-based dance steps to the sound of live drums. Since 1992, it's been internationally known as one of the best cultural dance centers with a vast array of classes, including African, Caribbean, Brazilian, Haitian, Cuban and more. Djoniba Centre's staff boasts some of the most renowned master dance teachers and top drummers in the world. Teachers make it easy for everyone to learn in a noncompetitive, friendly environment for people of all ages and levels, from absolute beginners to advanced dancers.

column2: Drum Centre was founded in 1992 by the internationally-acclaimed dancer, drummer, musical composer and choreographer Djoniba Mouflet. DDDC was the first school in the USA to offer the best variety of African-based dance classes as well as Ballet, Jazz, Hip Hop, Belly dance and other dance forms. In 1992 The school was located in its own 9000 square foot space on 18th street with 4 studios and a recording studio, an african import store, offering hundreds of dance classes for adults and children with more than 200 renowned teachers. The DDC Kids Scholarship Fund has provided free dance and drumming classes to more than 1,500 children from low-income families.  In 2010, DDDC moved to Peridance Centre's new state of the art space on 13th street.  Djoniba Centre has earned numerous awards, including Best Dance Studio and Best School of the Year by The Village Voice, New York Magazine, Time Out NY and AM New York. It's been featured on CNN, ABC News, and in The NY Times",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/JbR6HzSIJ3abXxF-g0wR_w/l.jpg,28

Sun Closed","At Catalyst SPORT, our mission is to empower you to change your body and change your life by helping you to feel good, move well, and get strong. Our signature fitness program is Semi-Private Training, and it offers 100% personalized and customized fitness programs in an intimate 3:1 setting, coached by some of the best personal trainers in Manhattan. We've trained Olympic hopefuls, fitness newbies, people recovering from injuries, and everyone in between. If you're a human, you WILL benefit from restoring the authentic human movement that lives in your DNA. The facility also features an on-site clinic led by world renowned chiropractor, Dr. Kathy Dooley. Our clinicians combine manual therapy with movement drills to treat dysfunctional patterns that are the root cause of pain and dysfunctional movement patterns. We utilize cutting edge functional modalities, including the Selective Functional Movement Assessment (SFMA), NeuroKinetic Therapy (NKT), active stretching, restorative breathing, and Dynamic Neuromuscular Stabilization (DNS).

Catalyst SPORT was founded with a simple mission: we help people just like you live better lives by helping you to move better and get stronger. As personal trainers with thousands upon thousands of hours of experience, Catalyst Co-Founders Joe Boffi and Jason Kapnick came to realize a simple truth: clients who move better make faster progress and get hurt less than those with poor movement patterns (for example, think of the ability to squat deeply, or the flexibility to touch your toes). When we met world-renowned Chiropractor Dr. Kathy Dooley and the three of us founded Catalyst, the results were nothing short of magical: a gym that helps you get strong without hurting you

column1: 126,New York Budo Association,"500 8th Ave, Fl 12, New York, NY 10018",,NULL,newyorkbudoassociation.org,"Mon 6:00 am - 9:00 pm

Sun Closed","At this dojo (school) we study iaido ( pronounced e-i-do). Popularly known as the art of drawing the sword. These teachings have evolved from the warrior class know as samurai. The basic principal involves controlled, precise movements of drawing the sword from it's scabbard (saya), striking or cutting an opponent, removing blood from the blade (chuburi), and then replacing the sword in the scabbard.Iaido teaches the use of actual metal weaponry, these techniques are real (this is not a sport). These techniques are taught through forms (kata). We also have partner practice or sparring (kumadachi), where we use wooden swords (bokken). All students use an unsharpened sword (iaito) for safety reasons. We also practice cutting bamboo mats (tameshigiri), for this we use real sharpened swords under very close supervision.NYB is one of four schools in the US that teaches Ryushin Shouchi Ryu...

In the memory of Yoshitsune Otani Sensei (1929 - 2002), NYBA is a nonprofit organization (501(c) 3, whose mission is to practice and sustain the techniques, philosophies, and benefits of the Japanese martial arts. We are also promoting culture, physical and mental growth, health and well-being as well as non-denominational spirituality. These traditional Japanese arts are a Do (xe9x81x93) (or Tao in Chinese), a Way, through which one strives to reveal the true self. By bringing this true self forward, one is transformed, and so also is the world.  Our focus is the study of Iaido (xe5xb1x85xe5x90x88xe9x81x93) the drawing of the Japanese sword, specifically Ryushin Shouchi Ryu (xe6x9fxb3xe5xbfx83xe7x85xa7xe6x99xbaxe6xb5x81), under the guidance of Soke Kunikazu Yahagi (Honbu in Tokyo). The curriculum includes kata (solo practice), kumitachi (partner practice) and tameshigiri (practice cutting).Co-coordinating and developing physical actions with mental awareness via ancient spiritual techniques is as daunting as it is rewarding",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/kWd2Y4Ti2EQgcofrKidCEw/l.jpg,14

Established in 1999Bikram Yoga NYC opened its doors in August 1999 and became Manhattan's first Bikram Yoga Studio. Owners Donna Rubin and Jennifer Lobo had both been avid practitioners of Bikram Yoga in other cities and knew that no city needed Bikram Yoga more than New York. In choosing the first location, Donna Rubin, a former Broadway performer, felt that there was a need for a place for pre-show warm-up in the theater district as the theaters themselves offered no space for stretching. In its first year, many performers, musicians and stage workers filled the classes at the 8th avenue location as a new way to stretch, de-stress and stay in shape.Word quickly spread about the amazing benefits of Bikram Yoga and in in 2001, Bikram Yoga NYC opened two more studios on the upper west side and downtown. 161,Omulu Guanabara Capoeira NYC,"55-59 Chrystie St, Ste 308, New York, NY 10002",,NULL,,"Mon 7:00 pm - 9:00 pm

Sun Closed","Capoeira is an African-Brazilian art form that combines dance, martial arts, music and acrobatics. Africans in Brazil created Capoeira over 400 years ago as a way to defend themselves and maintain their culture in the face of the harsh and oppressive conditions of slavery. Capoeira and Capoeiristas - those who practice the art - have survived tremendous odds to develop their art form while facing discrimination from the upper and middle classes of Brazilian society. Capoeira was illegal to practice up until the early 1930s, when legendary Mestre Bimba founded the first legal Capoeira Academy and created a new, contemporary style of the art, Capoeira Regional. Practiced in a circle called a roda (pronounced ho-dah) and accompanied by live music, Capoeira can be graceful or combative as the situation dictates. Originally considered a lower class pastime, Capoeira is now a living art and profound social force throughout the world.

Omulu Guanabara group is led by world-renowned Capoeira masters, Mestre Preguixc3xa7a and Mestre Di Mola. After maintaining two separate Capoeira groups, the two Mestres joined forces and created Omulu Guanabara, one of the worlds most respected and recognized Capoeira schools. The group's mission is to promote the art of Capoeira through the development of high-quality training academies, professional performance groups, and community culture and education programs. Chapters include San Francisco, New York, Los Angeles, Chicago, Seattle, Wisconsin, Massachusetts, Minneapolis, Sweden, Brazil, Canada, Venezuela and Mexico.You do not need any prior knowledge to start - classes are mixed level and open to beginners. Classes begin with a series of Capoeira exercises and stretches to strengthen and warm-up the body. Individual Capoeira moves and sequences are then practiced in pairs or separately across the floor. The class ends with a roda - the circle in which Capoeira and music is played",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/W4hLPke3wScbUrkjhfCDbw/o.jpg,1

Sun 4:00 pm - 6:00 pm","Tactical Studies Group is engaged in the integration of six categories of study, training and practice. These are Philosophy, Policy, Logistics, Strategy, Tactics and Skills.Philosophy is the basis of the art. We do not teach religion or mysticism. Elements of East Asian culture are inherent in some skill sets, but our philosophy consists in the principles of the American Founding and its roots in the Enlightenment of Western and Northern Europe.Skills are divided into three categories: weapons skills, boxing and trapping skills, and grappling and tumbling skills. Weapons include firearms, and Japanese and Filipino edged and blunt weapons.Boxing and trapping skills include elements of karate, Estacada, and other methods.Grappling and tumbling skills include Aiki jujutsu and some elements of Judo, wrestling, and other methods.There is no competition. There are no provisions for children. Firearms trainees must be licensed and vetted.

Having returned from eight years of training in Japan and nearly three more in California, I resumed training under local instructors. I had acted as an assistant instructor for two of my teachers in Kyoto, Osaka and LA. They wanted me to open a branch dojo under their auspices when I returned to NYC. I was reluctant to do this, but during my first year back, several persons suggested that I open a school. I was approached by a few investors, whose offers I turned down with thanks. Then as now, there was a recession. I did odd jobs and  accepted a few private students. Gradually a small group of trainees evolved and I was encouraged and authorized by three of my teachers to teach professionally. This is the origin of the Tactical Studies Group",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/iDzfWA-ef-UT6Qe9qJ7QHA/l.jpg,0

Sun 10:00 am - 3:30 pm","The USA Shaolin Temple teaches Chan Philosophy through the core Shaolin disciplines of martial arts or action meditation: Gongfu (Kung Fu) Taiji Quan (Tai Chi) and Qigong (Chi Kung).  Students of all backgrounds, religions, ages, and athletic ability can train at Temple. Students come to the USA Shaolin Temple from all around the world to learn and grow from traditional Shaolin training. Heart to Heart and Mind to Mind is the essence of Shaolin Chan Philosophy -- and this system of training spans the differences between language and culture as a direct form of growth and understanding. Students find many paths to get to the Temple

Fri  & 5/29/2020 Closed","Welcome to Orangetheory Fitness, the energizing group interval fitness concept that is sweeping the nation! Orangetheory Fitness is a one-of-a-kind workout broken into intervals of cardiovascular and strength training, using a variety of equipment including treadmills, rowing, TRX straps, and free weights to tone your body and gain energy throughout the day.

The physiological theory behind the Orangetheory workout is known as Excess Post-Exercise Oxygen Consumption, or EPOC. By providing you with a heart rate monitor and POD, we can monitor your 5 zone interval training sessions that we call the Orange 60. During the 60 minute workout, you will perform multiple intervals designed to produce12 minutes or more of training at 84% or higher of your maximum heart rate, which translates to Zones 4/5. This program design produces EPOC, which is the workout after-burn effect, meaning that our interval training design produces a 200-400 calorie increase to your metabolism 24-36 hours after your workout",https://house-fastly.us-east-1.ooyala.com/RpcDNkajE6guNGOCOKeTqxpTa4J04IkR/Ut_HKthATH4eww8X4xMDoxOjBhOzV3Va,8

This dance-fitness series uses *soca* music of the Caribbean that is fused with other genres like pop, hip hop, reggae, zouk, salsa, dancehall and more to bring the spirit and movement of the Carnival into the routine.  Classes highlight different aspects of the festival and show the diversity of the Caribbean as it changes each season.  Tone your arms with fun movements in SocaFlagsxe2x84xa2. Founder, Onya West, is a certified group fitness instructor with Caribbean heritage who has a unique background in dance, sports, medicine and public health. She developed SocaMotion Fitness and Wellness as a way to celebrate the culture and diversity of the Caribbean while making exercise fun by using aspects of the Carnival festivals and traditional dances of the region.  The series of dance-fitness classes turn your workout into a Carnival with the music and use of accessories of Carnival in unique ways to produce results on your body.  The SocaSLIMDOWN weight loss challenge uses Caribbean cuisine to make diet food healthy.   The movement started in Brooklyn in 2010 and made its home on Eastern Parkway where Labor Day Carnival is held in New York every year.  Classes are also available at other sites in Brooklyn, Queens and Manhattan and the craze is catching on even in other states and countries.  Be a SocaMover today!...Move Your Mas",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/lh1yBdUSLw5GexGbilqdUQ/l.jpg,0

Sun Closed","Restore Performance Physical Therapy is not just a physical therapy office.  It begins with the base of PT and encompasses an expanded profile of complimentary services and therapies to fully address the individual needs of the patient. Our treatments include:Physical TherapyMassage therapy/manual therapiesYoga/Thai YogaOne-to-one exercise trainingWe treat a variety of conditions, ranging from Pre/post-natal dysfunctions, to Rhetumatic conditions, (fibromyalgia, rheumatic arthritis), sports-specific conditions, and pain or discomfort related to a specific activity such as sitting, exercising, working or sleeping.

Raymond Silva, PTRaymond Silva has been a physical therapist for over 15 years. He first became interested in physical therapy in high school when his grandmother's sister suffered a stroke. Her everyday function was a struggle. When she began receiving treatment from three PT students working as clinical interns, Raymond watched them as they tried to improve her physical condition and made sure she was comfortable with any treatment they did. The therapists were able to have her walking with a walker (having standby assistance), after she was unable to stand. Following, he thought this is something he could see himself doing, as how could there be a better profession than this: providing a service to people and improving their function/lives after sustaining injury or having a condition that caused changes, which led to a decline in a person's physical ability to function, may it be secondary to pain, limitation of motion, or weakness",,0

Sun Closed","Corinthian Physical Therapy was established in 1992 as one of the first one on one, hourly manual therapy private practices in New York City. That means they observe and assess your whole body and concentrate on the interconnections of all body parts, treating the source of the problems and not just the symptoms. Many of Corinthian Therapy patients receiving physical therapy progress to a one on one Pilates-based exercise program in our private, open air Pilates studio which includes state of the art equipment including the Balance Body Pilates reformer, wunda chair, and spring board.

Sun Closed","Mark Greenfield, owner of On Your Mark Sports Massage and Fitness, provides clinical massage therapy and customized personal training to help clients feel, look and perform their best. Whether you are struggling with an injury, getting ready to graduate from physical therapy, training for a specific sport or just want to remain injury and pain-free, or all of the above, Mark can utilize a unique and dynamic combination of hands-on treatments and specialized workouts to help you reach your goals. As one of the few Licensed Massage Therapists (LMT) and Certified Personal Trainers (CPT) who also provides Active Release Techniques (ART), he's uniquely qualified in the field. ART is an advanced clinical, movement-based manual therapy system designed to treat muscle, nerve and joint pain. Mark's use of ART can help you with everything from carpal tunnel to chronic back pain, muscle strains, tendonitis, plantar fascitis, shin splints, sciatica, ITB pain, TMJ dysfunction, rotator cuff injuries, shoulder impingement and much more.  And his expertise in complementary techniques like deep tissue massage and myofascial release as well as his expertise in personal training and corrective exercises allows Mark to offer a wide range of services for clients.

Over the past decade, Mark has provided hundreds of clients with thousands of massages, Active Release treatments and innovative workouts. With his expertise and personalized care, he's helped them to recover from injuries, manage their pain, and perform better at work and in sports. He looks forward to many more years of helping others to live up to their physical potential!",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/_bNv1e6CPtgUaKJRG05Bgg/l.jpg,13

Sun 8:15 am - 3:45 pm","Mark Fisher Fitness is NOT for everyone - and we're not afraid to say it. We believe the key to a positive health and hotness experience is great coaching and program design in a fun, inclusive atmosphere. However, we fully understand not everyone will find our style of training or zany fun to be for them. We tend to curse a lot, we tell a lot of silly (and often risquxc3xa9) jokes as teaching tools, and we spend as much time laughing as we do grunting with effort. We don't use (or believe in) fancy machines, we prize technique and safety over simply getting exhausted, and we believe in training HARD and actually getting results. If this isn't for you, we wish you the best in your fitness journey! But if you think you'd benefit from some quality time with ridiculous humans who are serious about fitness... we just might be a match made in fitness heaven. (The MFF team gives you a warm hug followed by a crisp high five.)

Beyond Pilates / Integrated Fitness Center owner, Ed Morand, got his start as an instructor at  the NY Sports Clubs/Town Sport Int'l chain.  After a quick rise to Master Trainer status he soon became a member of their Training and Development faculty responsible for educating both Pilates instructors and personal trainers in the fundamentals of fitness and exercise science .  It is this fusion of state-of-the-art ideas which gave rise to Beyond Pilates/Integrated Fitness Center.  Morand noticed a need for greater inclusion of the fitness sciences in Pilates exercise selection and program design.  While he also noticed that fitness instructors and personal trainers might benefit by adding the qualitative elements of Pilates technique to their work. Sun Open 24 hours","Here you'll find high-quality tango shoes for men and women that are professionally customized, feature an innovative heel reinforcement, and crafted with top-grade leather. Our shoes combine stability, comfort, and flexibility creating a tango dance experience that enables the most difficult movements with grace and precision.We specialized in custom made orders. You can personalize your shoes by selecting heel height and thickness, materials, padding, and more. To ensure the most accurate fit, your size will be determined by the measurements of your feet. Express your creativity by customizing your shoes or choose from our unique stock for men and women through our online store or by visiting our showroom in NYC by appointment only.Our shoes can be made for any occasion as well as for the different type of dancings as Flamenco, Salsa, and Jazz.

After many years of performances, instruction, and practice, Yaisuri Salamanca became aware of the importance of having the most correct dance shoes. Here is her story:It has always been really hard for me to buy shoes. My size is not on the shoe retail market. I couldn't find shoes that fit and most shoe retailers have little patience for special orders. One time, I won a prize from a competition in Argentina. The prize was a pair of tango shoes. I received my voucher and went with excitement to claim my prize. I was so excited to see so many beautiful tango shoes. I tried one pair after another, but I ended up getting a pair that was the less painful to wear. It was then that I decided to create my own line of professional dance shoes for men and women. I focused on stylish-functional designs which combine beauty, comfort, and stability. I established my business in the year 2011 even though I have been working with custom orders since 2005",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/_Kv9f75ohQyqGkNFvn5c4A/l.jpg,3

Thu  & 5/28/2020 Closed","Welcome to Orangetheory Fitness, the energizing group interval fitness concept that is sweeping the nation! Orangetheory Fitness is a one-of-a-kind workout broken into intervals of cardiovascular and strength training, using a variety of equipment including treadmills, rowing, TRX straps, and free weights to tone your body and gain energy throughout the day.

The physiological theory behind the Orangetheory workout is known as Excess Post-Exercise Oxygen Consumption, or EPOC. By providing you with a heart rate monitor and POD, we can monitor your 5 zone interval training sessions that we call the Orange 60. During the 60 minute workout, you will perform multiple intervals designed to produce12 minutes or more of training at 84% or higher of your maximum heart rate, which translates to Zones 4/5. This program design produces EPOC, which is the workout after-burn effect, meaning that our interval training design produces a 200-400 calorie increase to your metabolism 24-36 hours after your workout",https://house-fastly.us-east-1.ooyala.com/RpcDNkajE6guNGOCOKeTqxpTa4J04IkR/Ut_HKthATH4eww8X4xMDoxOjBhOzV3Va,88

Sun Closed","Functional Training is the engagement in exercises that mimic or recreate everyday movement. These types of exercises typically involve the use of your full body and multiple muscle groups. This style of training builds and sculpts lean, functional muscle and all can be found at F45 Training. The fixed, 45 minute duration of our workouts exists to provide a timing structure to maximize our members' growth and progress. Our daily workouts vary the amount of exercise stations, the Work Time / Rest Time ratio and the number of repetitions through the Exercise Circuit of each day. This provides a challenging workout for our clientele that is always evolving and never the same. The motivation and encouragement in a Group Training facility create a pulsing, upbeat environment where goals are met and exceeded. Communities promoting fitness, good health and growth are forged in F45 studios around the world and are the source of our strength as an international brand.

F45 is a revolutionary training system changing lives around the globe. Our decades-tested circuit training model focuses on whole body workouts with an emphasis on weight-bearing exercise and functional movements, a concentration not found in other popular regimens. With 500+ digitally presented programs, you will never see the same program twice, freeing our professional coaches to focus on safety, technique, and personal pace. This allows us to adapt to all levels of fitness while providing an optimum exercise experience for all. column1: Established over two decades ago by Sue Hee Ko (Director).  Studios located in Garden Grove, Orange County, Northridge, and Los Angeles. 709,Orangetheory Fitness Koreatown,"687 Hobart Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 90005",(213) 943-3007,NULL,orangetheoryfitness.com,,"Welcome to Orangetheory Fitness, the energizing group interval fitness concept that is sweeping the nation! Orangetheory Fitness is a one-of-a-kind workout broken into intervals of cardiovascular and strength training, using a variety of equipment including treadmills, rowing, TRX straps, and free weights to tone your body and gain energy throughout the day.

The physiological theory behind the Orangetheory workout is known as Excess Post-Exercise Oxygen Consumption, or EPOC. By providing you with a heart rate monitor and POD, we can monitor your 5 zone interval training sessions that we call the Orange 60. During the 60 minute workout, you will perform multiple intervals designed to produce 12 minutes or more of training at 84% or higher of your maximum heart rate, which translates to Zones 4/5. This program design produces EPOC, which is the workout after-burn effect, meaning that our interval training design produces a 200-400 calorie increase to your metabolism 24-36 hours after your workout",https://house-fastly.us-east-1.ooyala.com/RpcDNkajE6guNGOCOKeTqxpTa4J04IkR/Ut_HKthATH4eww8X4xMDoxOjBhOzV3Va,8

column1: 745,CorePower Yoga,"1031 Glendon Ave, Los Angeles, CA 90024",(213) 810-3153,NULL,corepoweryoga.com,"Mon 6:00 am - 10:00 pm

Thu  & 5/28/2020 Closed","Breathe, flow, sweat - together. Discover the magic that happens when physical meets mindful. The power of practice is yours - wherever you are. While our 200+ studios are temporarily closed, keep up your practice from home. Subscribe to access 300+ online yoga, sculpt and meditation classes with CorePower Yoga On Demand. Or connect in real-time classes streaming 7 days a week on CorePower Live where we can flow together - even when apart. And tune into Instagram and Instagram Live @corepoweryoga for daily moments of yoga and mindfulness. #LiveYourPower

When a serious climbing accident left him with six permanent screws in his shattered ankle, CorePower Yoga Founder and CEO Trevor Tice experienced first hand the benefits of yoga.  An avid outdoorsman, Trevor was left searching for an exercise to replace the running, climbing and other physically challenging activities no longer accessible to him.  He found yoga and was hooked.  In 2002, Trevor opened the first CorePower Yoga studio on Grant Street in downtown Denver, Colorado.  CorePower Yoga strives to increase awareness and widespread adoption of yoga by making yoga accessible to everyone, through a variety of yoga styles, for beginners and more advanced yoga students, and yoga class times to meet any schedule.CorePower Yoga provides a challenging yoga class that allows our students to see benefits in all areas of their lives",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/vJ5dZRs3i8NMr1zubgMZFw/l.jpg,77

Sun Closed","The Insight Center brings together traditional Buddhist teachings, mindfulness meditation and somatic therapy.   We teach traditional mindfulness meditation and body psychotherapy workshops.   Our trainings are for the general public and  psychotherapists.  We provide psychotherapy to individuals, couples and families.  Our goal is to help our students and clients to lead fulfilling lives.

The Insight Center grew out of LA Dharma, a non-sectarian Buddhist meditation organization. Through LA Dharma we hosted meditation retreats, sitting groups and mindfulness classes from 2000 to 2006.  In 2006, we acquired our physical space and formed the Insight Center to continue the legacy of LA Dharma while offering somatic practices to more deeply support our students. With our permanent home, we began to offer clinical trainings and psychotherapy services, and in October 2007, we launched our Continuing Education Program for mental health professionals with authorization from the American Psychological Association, the California Board of Behavioral Sciences and the California Board of Registered Nursing.While we continue to offer classical Buddhist teachings and courses in mindfulness meditation, our clinical specialty focuses on healing early developmental trauma. We collaborate with some of the nation's foremost clinicians and teachers, and have recently expanded our faculty",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/B-k8h5hjbt_stxja90z10g/l.jpg,2

820,UCLA Center for Human Nutrition RFO Weight Management Program,900 Weyburn Pl, Ste 14-171, Warren Hall Room, Los Angeles, CA 90095",(310) 825-8173,NULL,uclahealth.org,"Mon Closed

Sun Closed","UCLA Center for Human Nutrition RFO Weight Management Program is a medically-supervised state-of-the-art University-based multidisciplinary program first established in 1976. For over 30 years this program has provided personalized programs for weight loss in obese and moderately overweight patients especially in individuals with obesity-associated illnesses and conditions including pre-diabetes, diabetes, high cholesterol and blood lipids, heart disease, breast, prostate, and colon cancer survivors, asthma, sleep disorders, and autoimmune diseases.Our physicians are David Heber, MD, PhD, Zhaoping Li, MD, PhD, Stefanie Fein, MD, Richard Kachel, MD, Mehran Kashefi, MD, and Vijaya Surampudi, MD.

The RFO Program has been in operation for more than 25 years (originated in the mid-1970's by Morton H. Maxwell, M.D.). The RFO Program was one of the first university programs to perform research and clinically practice the use of very low calorie diets (VLCD) in the treatment of severe obesity. This program was among the first to utilize prescription appetite-suppressants as an integral component of obesity treatment",,8

Sun 7:00 am - 5:00 pm","Westwood Pilates is a Classical Pilates studio fully equipped with Gratz apparatus (original manufacturer of authentic Pilates equipment), providing both Private sessions and Group Classes. Now considered one of the best and only Classical Pilates studios in West Los Angeles, our studio has become known to create very personalized relationships with our clients.

Each year since our founding in 2013, Westwood Pilates has grown, creating a community of Pilates enthusiasts and a home away from home from beginners to seasoned teachers. We aim to provide a space where people feel comfortable and welcome, no matter what your age, ethnicity, gender, body type, or movement background.The Pilates Method is an exercise technique developed by Joseph Pilates (1880 - 1967). He drew inspiration from both eastern and western exercise regimes and created a sequence of exercises on various pieces of equipment that connect body and mind, focus on the proper use of breath and a strong center. After our meeting we will go to the court for a full evaluation which is documented on video for future review. When the evaluation is complete we will discuss anything we see that needs to be improved upon, what needs to be done to correct them and how it's going to be done step-by-step. Sun Closed","I am physical therapist who veered out of the traditional medical model into an educational approach.  I am now a Guild Certified Feldenkrais Practitioner. I teach baby boomers how to become experts on themselves and live the life they want. This work is helpful in helping you to get rid of back pain, knee pain, hip pain, and live your life in spite of any itis you may have. Your pain will decrease and when it comes on, you will know what to do. I work with people individually, teach weekly classes, and monthly workshops. Contact me for a free phone consultation

When I finished PT school I wanted to save the world. My interest seemed to go to those people who did not get better with the cookbook approach. I searched many alternative methods until I found the Feldenkrais Method. I already knew that movement and health comes from the brain, not the muscles. If we want to feel better we must change how our brain perceives pain and its relationship to what we do, how we move. I finished my extensive Feldenkrais Training in 1991 and have been teaching this method since. I love what I do!",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/tECHOG268Xl54SZK5SZ8rg/o.jpg,2

column1: Mindful awareness can be defined as paying attention to present moment experiences with openness, curiosity, and a willingness to be with what is. It is an excellent antidote to the stresses of modern times. It invites us to stop, breathe, observe, and connect with one's inner experience. There are many ways to bring mindfulness into one's life, such as meditation, yoga, art, or time in nature. Mindfulness can be trained systematically, and can be implemented in daily life, by people of any age, profession or background.In the last ten years, significant research has shown mindfulness to address health issues such as lower blood pressure and boost the immune system

941,Sultan Yoga,Los Angeles, CA 90012",,NULL,sultanyoga.com,,"I am Aruna Sultan, and I am a certified yoga instructor. My specialty is developing a personalized practice to fit each student's needs. I am currently accepting new students for private sessions in Los Angeles, and I can come to your place to teach you yoga in the comfort of your own home. My teaching style incorporates modern understanding of neuroscience, knowledge of anatomy and insights from Iyengar yoga, Tai Chi and Feldenkrais.

I started taking group yoga classes in New York city in 2005. This was something I did to get stronger, more flexible and more resilient to stress from a fast pace life in the Big Apple. Although I enjoyed the effects of yoga, I did not develop full appreciation for it till I met a dear friend of mine and an accomplished yogi, Eric Powell. It was him who introduced Ramaswami's works to me. It took me many months before I actually took a look at the book Eric recommended, The Complete Book of Vinyasa Yoga. When I moved to San Francisco in January 2010, I thought I should check out Ramaswami's teachings at Esalen Institute. In May 2010, I took a 5 day Hatha Yoga Practicum with Srivatsa Ramaswami at Esalen and immediately decided to continue my studies with him.  In June of that year I went to Los Angeles to study with him for 5 weeks at the Vinyasa Krama Teacher Training Program.  Here I am, teaching Vinyasa Krama and absolutely loving it!",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Dk1Y3zdvsgYsfhQ9LwhVww/l.jpg,15

The Aikido Center of Los Angeles was founded in 1974 by Reverend Kensho Furuya.  The late Rev. Kensho Furuya was a 6th Dan in Hombu Aikido and 6th Dan Kyoshi in Muso Shinden Ryu Iaido, with over 47 years experience in the martial artist. Furuya Sensei earned his degrees in Asian Studies at the University of Southern California and Harvard University. He trained at the Aikido World Headquarters in Tokyo, Japan in 1969, under the late Kisshomaru Ueshiba Doshu and established his Dojo in 1974. Furuya Sensei was ordained as a Zen priest in 1988 and received the honor to speak at the United Nations in the following year. He was the author of many articles on martial arts and has appeared on many television programs speaking on the subject. He authored the book Kodo: Ancient Ways, and the acclaimed video series, The Art of Aikido which is in nine volumes",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/OeItXa-gBp7IjY1Vt6NSOQ/o.jpg,8

Sun Closed","Krav Maga is not a traditional martial art. It was developed in an environment where the Israeli military could not devote many hours to hand to hand combat training. Therefore, the Krav Maga system was created to bring students to a high level of skill in a relatively short period of time. Krav Maga There are no forms (katas) or rules or set combinations as reactions to attacks. Instead, Krav Maga training focuses on teaching simple self-defense techniques which are specifically catered to reality based attack situations. Many techniques originated in Muay Thai, kickboxing, boxing and wrestling, with other techniques call from Ju-Jitsu and Karate.

Sun Closed","Orlando Chiropractic is dedicated to helping patients reach an optimal level of health and wellness. Each patient has a unique set of symptoms and goals which require a treatment program designed specifically for them. Too often, the source of injury is not addressed, especially with regard to the musuloskeletal system. Pills are prescribed and short term treatments are used to help alleviate the pain in specific areas. Unfortunately, the overall physical dysfunction is not considered and the patient often has recurring symptoms and additional injuries. Our approach is to work with patients to address the core problem and develop a course of treatment to correct it.

Thu  & 5/28/2020 Closed","Welcome to Orangetheory Fitness, the energizing group interval fitness concept that is sweeping the nation! Orangetheory Fitness is a one-of-a-kind workout broken into intervals of cardiovascular and strength training, using a variety of equipment including treadmills, rowing, TRX straps, and free weights to tone your body and gain energy throughout the day.

The physiological theory behind the Orangetheory workout is known as Excess Post-Exercise Oxygen Consumption, or EPOC. By providing you with a heart rate monitor and POD, we can monitor your 5 zone interval training sessions that we call the Orange 60. During the 60 minute workout, you will perform multiple intervals designed to produce12 minutes or more of training at 84% or higher of your maximum heart rate, which translates to Zones 4/5. This program design produces EPOC, which is the workout after-burn effect, meaning that our interval training design produces a 200-400 calorie increase to your metabolism 24-36 hours after your workout",https://house-fastly.us-east-1.ooyala.com/RpcDNkajE6guNGOCOKeTqxpTa4J04IkR/Ut_HKthATH4eww8X4xMDoxOjBhOzV3Va,46

Thu  & 5/28/2020 Closed","Welcome to Orangetheory Fitness, the energizing group interval fitness concept that is sweeping the nation! Orangetheory Fitness is a one-of-a-kind workout broken into intervals of cardiovascular and strength training, using a variety of equipment including treadmills, rowing, TRX straps, and free weights to tone your body and gain energy throughout the day.

The physiological theory behind the Orangetheory workout is known as Excess Post-Exercise Oxygen Consumption, or EPOC. By providing you with a heart rate monitor and POD, we can monitor your 5 zone interval training sessions that we call the Orange 60. During the 60 minute workout, you will perform multiple intervals designed to produce12 minutes or more of training at 84% or higher of your maximum heart rate, which translates to Zones 4/5. This program design produces EPOC, which is the workout after-burn effect, meaning that our interval training design produces a 200-400 calorie increase to your metabolism 24-36 hours after your workout",https://house-fastly.us-east-1.ooyala.com/RpcDNkajE6guNGOCOKeTqxpTa4J04IkR/Ut_HKthATH4eww8X4xMDoxOjBhOzV3Va,65

1061,Crunch Fitness - Chatsworth,20914 Nordhoff St, Chatsworth, CA 91311",(818) 775-0300,NULL,crunch.com,,"The Crunch gym in Chatsworth, CA fuses fitness and fun with certified personal trainers, awesome group fitness classes, a no judgments philosophy, and gym memberships.

Of all the great histories of all the great health clubs, Crunch's begins rather inauspiciously: in a basement level aerobics studio in New York City's East Village circa 1989. We were on an important mission - to make exercise fun. And, accomplishing this mission meant doing away with traditional notions of what a 'serious' workout should be.What we did was invite a highly creative group of fitness instructors with a wide range of expertise to collaborate with us. The result was the development of challenging programming with a completely fresh slant. Offerings like Hip-Hop Aerobics, Co-Ed Action Wrestling and Cyked Yoga Cycling were introduced and, along with others, became the embodiment of this new approach.Fast-forward, more than two decades later, Crunch is still a gym that believes in making serious exercise fun by fusing fitness and entertainment and holding true to a philosophy of No Judgments",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/BscVn_04p3aTe9xQaTWUaA/l.jpg,341

Sun 7:30 am - 8:30 pm","Going on 15 years the Elite Volleyball Club has excelled in both physical and athletic development. We are the honors class of club volleyball, giving youth athletes who are highly motivated to learn and progress in leaps and bounds, the ability to do so. Our travel teams include unlimited gym time for every player, private lessons, small group training, team practices, literally 7 day a week availability. For our local teams, we include the access to crossover to other teams and practice so they can test the water. Players can schedule practice sessions with older and younger elite or local teams to work with different coaches, players and levels of play. There is no other club in the country that offers these types of opportunities. Our club director is the only player to ever come out of the San Fernando Valley area and earn a top 10 ranking as a hitter in womens division I volleyball, and earn a top 15 ranking in back to back years, and she was trained by Elite. Our most recent star is playing at UCLA, and our top player from this past season, 2015 is headed off to the University of Hawaii for athletic scholarship. We have created a training regimen that prepares players to do great things at the collegiate level, and almost guarantees college scholarship if you are willing to put in the time and work. Our Elite players can teach volleyball as well as they play it, and we make education a huge part of our training.

Elite has come up through the ranks of the volleyball world. Starting with a group of players that were turned away from other clubs for not being experienced enough and developing them into the top 17's team in the area and earning the regional bid to the Junior Olympics. Since that time we have continued to elevate our training standards and protocols and continue to set the standard in both physical and technical training. column1: 1079,Janjira Fitness,"7138 Shoup Ave, Ste B6, West Hills, CA 91307",(818) 961-2600,NULL,,"Mon 5:00 pm - 9:00 pm

Sun Closed","The martial art that is taught at Janjira Fitness is a mixture of Muay Thai, the combat sport from Thailand, kickboxing from Japan, and American boxing. Our programs include high intensity cardiovascular workouts which include stretching, breathing, focus, and conditioning for all our members. Our style includes the art of eight limbs which includes hand, feet, elbow, and knee combinations as part of our curriculum. Our philosophy is to learn all the same basics and philosophies of a world champion from the beginning. Doesn't matter whether you're a kid or an adult, come and experience the heat and burn calories with the best in the business. First-timers, come and experience a free class and train with  professional Coach Victor Alvarez, and BCBC State Champion Kevin Gonzalez all mentored by legendary trainer and manager Coach David Krapes.

In 2011, Janjira Fitness was formerly known as Where Champions Are Made and was founded by 12-Time Welterweight World Champion Hector Pena The Aztec Warrior. In 2015, he passed away and his legacy was continued by legends' fighter trainer Coach David Krapes and partner Rob Harper of Harper's Bar and Grill. They rebranded the gym to Janjira Fitness and kept Where Champions Are Made as the motto. The name Janjira is synonymous with the legendary Thai fighter from Thailand, Saekson Janjira, who David had worked closely with and helped train. Saekson operates his business today in Dallas, Texas. Today, we continue the legacy by mentoring our students under the philosophies of Muay Thai and kickboxing. Type 2 is what gives a ballerina a lean but rock solid appearance and it is only created through explosive mevement. Sun Closed","My approach to physical therapy starts with an assessment of one's biomechanics, posture, joint and soft tissue mobility and range of motion and strength.  I get a good idea of how a person moves to determine from the beginning what may be contributing cause of the onset of pain (other than an obvious injury).  I then focus on hands-on techniques to relieve pain quickly, using myofascial release and cupping as needed.  Once pain is reduced, focus moves to the biomechanical aspects, rom and strength deficits that contribute to the onset of pain.  I use pilates and yoga as well as DNS and Janda techniques (more information found on my website.) With nearly 20 years of experience I've seen it al.  I treat all post surgical cases, including total hip and knee replacements (tkr, thr), all painful movement dysfunctions from the neck to the ankles and everything in between, including arthritis.  As an athlete who has dealt with pain, I've learned what works best for quick results. I love my geriatric (Medicare) physical therapy clients as well. They often need patience and time and a gentle hand.I also do home visits for cash, Medicare and ppo blue shield clients.

This company was developed in 2013 with the mission of providing excellent physical therapy care as well as wellness services, including nutritional and herbal advice to improve overall health",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/GOnTRIPyj_tXJXjNoFzRqg/l.jpg,5

Sun Closed","About UsSheila Hughes M.D. Wellness and Weight Loss in the Brentwood neighborhood of Los Angeles, California, has helped more than 5,000 patients reach their weight-loss goals. Led by board-certified physician and weight management expert Sheila Hughes, MD, the practice is dedicated to personalized care in a positive, judgment-free environment.Dr. Hughes has personal experience with significant weight loss and has dedicated her life to helping others achieve a positive relationship with nutrition and exercise. She understands that food-based behaviors and emotional eating are often signs of a person's negative relationship with food. That's why Dr. Hughes and her team work to break these patterns and help their patients take back control of their bodies.From a three-phase nutrition plan and regular vitamin B12 injections to FDA-approved appetite suppressants and supplements, Dr. Hughes and her team can create a personalized weight-loss plan that helps you healthily shed weight without deprivation. Dr. Hughes is proud to guide her patients through their weight-loss journeys. She understands that weight loss is a very personal experience, which is why she makes it a point to meet her patients for weekly visits during treatment.In addition to a variety of weight-loss services, Sheila Hughes M.D. Wellness and Weight Loss provides several body-sculpting treatments, including truSculptxc2xae iD, Plus by InMode, and Body FX...

Dr. Hughes, who refers to herself as a reformed yo-yo dieter, has a better design for releasing weight. She originally honed her skills as a family practice physician with 28 years of experience in a location she affectionately refers to as Carbohydrate Heaven, surrounded by Burger King, Kentucky Fried Chicken, Sonic, and of course, McDonald's!Dr. Hughes is a graduate of Temple Medical School in Philadelphia, with medical training at the University of Maryland Hospital and The Medical Center in Columbus, Georgia. Sun Closed","My approach to physical therapy starts with an assessment of one's biomechanics, posture, joint and soft tissue mobility and range of motion and strength.  I get a good idea of how a person moves to determine from the beginning what may be contributing cause of the onset of pain (other than an obvious injury).  I then focus on hands-on techniques to relieve pain quickly, using myofascial release and cupping as needed.  Once pain is reduced, focus moves to the biomechanical aspects, rom and strength deficits that contribute to the onset of pain.  I use pilates and yoga as well as DNS and Janda techniques (more information found on my website.) I treat all post surgical cases, including  total hip and knee replacements (tkr, thr), all painful movement dysfunctions from the neck to the ankles and everything in between, including arthritis.  As an athlete who has dealt with pain, I've learned what works best for quick results. I love my geriatric (Medicare) physical therapy clients as well. They often need patience and time and a gentle hand.I also do home visits for cash, Medicare and ppo blue shield clients.

Since the year 2000, Anne McArthur has been a professional beach volleyball player, using her experience as an athlete and a patient to develop a great understanding of pain and how to eliminate it.  She has been working with all types of cases and all ages for over 18 years in various locations across Los Angeles.  She discovered cupping more than 10 years ago and has developed her own techniques for every body part.  She has an excellent reputation for being able to quickly relieve your pain, and uses pilates and yoga based exercises, as well as her own therapeutic inventions in her rehabilitation programs.  After working at the International Orthopedic Center for Joint disorders for 15 years Anne opened her own practice, Holistic Physical Therapy and Wellness, Inc. located at 12401 Wilshire Blvd, Ste 205, Los angeles, CA 90025.   She is also doing personalized home physical therapy visits, so if you can't get out the house, the therapy can come to you!",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/kQ-Nsx4_dGSNip5Ng93XKw/l.jpg,9

Sun 10:00 am - 6:00 pm","My approach is to merge Eastern and Western healing modalities that utilize the body's wisdom to heal itself. The various techniques I use integrates ancient eastern wisdom with western scientific and psychological understanding. They cover a wide range of body-oriented therapies from strongly physical, deep-tissue massage to the most subtle energy work.Each of the practices explores the art of flow: the natural, effortless unwinding of our lives in a way that moves us toward wholeness and harmony. Its focus is to cultivate harmonious, balanced movement and flow rhythm on all levels, such as physical, emotional, mental, energetic, and spiritual. Flow is central to my work because it is essential to our health and well-being. Communication and coordination between all of our parts require the smooth flow of biochemical and electromagnetic signals through our fluids, tissues, and bones. The fluidity of our emotions and thoughts enables us to harmonize our inner world and to be flexible and resilient in our dealings with the outer world. Increased awareness in the art of flow invites us to connect with our inherent capacity to heal. Harmonious flow is relevant in today's world, not only for our health but also for our relationships, careers, and personal growth - we can become more healthy, connected, abundant, and energized.

I am also one of the founders of Padma NYC meditation and holistic center along with Nicholas Waterfall. Our love and passion are to create a safe, aesthetic environment where people can relax and heal, returning to their daily lives recharged and better able to face the challenges of living in a big urban environment like New York City. Padma NYC is an oasis in the heart of the city for meditation and the healing arts. Here we combine the wisdom of the East with the science of the West. Sun Closed","SwimJim, Inc.'s teaching methodology is a safe, thoughtful, ordered approach to swimming, cultivating proficiency in a number of strokes. We believe the success with which our current and past students navigate the water proves our program's effectiveness.The most important aspect of our teaching process is our disciplined but loving dedication to getting children in and comfortable with the water. We are thoughtful and observant of student's behavioral and developmental patterns, and will never scare or intimidate a student. We will respond to their fears and concerns with love, humor and discipline, while guiding them through the necessary steps to become independent, competent swimmers.We deeply enjoy helping with children with special needs and development issues.  They are some of our favorite and best students! Kavi Yogi Swarananda Mani Finger and his son, Alan Finger, created ISHTA Yoga in the late 1960s in South Africa. Seeking to integrate and celebrate the different teachings and lineages that passed through their ashram, Mani and Alan created ISHTA Yoga.In 1975, Alan moved to the United States, settling in Los Angeles and co-founding Yoga Works. In 1993, Alan relocated to New York City and formed the Yoga Zone studios. Yoga Zone became Be Yoga and expanded Alan's teachings into one of the most successful regional yoga teacher training programs in the country. Coming full circle, in 2004 Be Yoga rejoined the Yoga Works family of studios.As the culmination of his life-long development of ISHTA, Alan and his partners opened the first ISHTA Yoga studio in Manhattan in May 2008, at 56 East 11th Street. For the first time, all elements of the ISHTA tradition had a dedicated home. In February 2011, ISHTA opened the doors to its uptown studio, located at 1026 Third Avenue",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/702MTt9mBNyt91EFdb7Qog/l.jpg,119

Sun 8:00 am - 10:00 pm","The mission of the Ailey organization is to further the pioneering vision of the choreographer, dancer, and cultural leader Alvin Ailey (1931-1989) by building an extended cultural community which provides dance performances, training and education, and community programs for all people. This performing arts community plays a crucial social role, using the beauty and humanity of the African American heritage and other cultures to unite people of all races, ages and backgrounds.

Alvin Ailey American Dance Theater grew from a now-fabled performance in 1958 at the 92nd St Y in New York City. Led by Alvin Ailey and a group of young African American modern dancers, that performance changed forever the perception of American dance. The Ailey company has gone on to perform for an estimated 25 million people at theaters in 48 states and 71 countries on six continents xe2x80x93 as well as millions more through TV broadcasts, film screenings, and online platforms. The Ailey organization also encompasses four other major programs: Ailey II, a performing company that represents the next generation of dance
column2: The Ailey School, which provides world class training to over 1,400 students each year
column3: Ailey Arts In Education &amp
column4: Community Programs, which helps over 60,000 people of all ages take, make, and see dance

1510,Unnata® Aerial Yoga,163 Bleecker St, Fl 2, New York, NY 10012",(212) 533-9642,NULL,aerialyoga.com/unnata-classes-…,,"If you want to take group Unnataxc2xae Aerial Yoga classes, visit the Sacred Brooklyn Yoga center (Village location) at the listed address and phone number. You can find the schedule of classes at the Sacred Brooklyn website.If you want to take private or semi-private (up to 3 people) Unnataxc2xae Aerial Yoga classes, visit the small home studio of Founder, Michelle Dortignac, in the Clinton Hill area of Brooklyn. You can find more information on the Unnata website. If you want to practice at home, you can find downloadable videos on the Unnata website on the Vimeo page. We have made some videos for people who don't have a hammock at home, too.For your comfort, we recommend wearing clothing that covers the back of the knees and the armpits. Also try to avoid low-cut and/or loose clothing as clothing may shift around when upside-down. Learn how to achieve proper postural alignment through relaxation rather than effort, enhancing a peaceful state of mind.Unnata Aerial Yoga supports your traditional Yoga practice in the following ways:    * Challenging traditional Yoga postures such as inversions and deep backbends can be achieved without effort and without strain.    * Deep muscle releases achieved in the air allow students to explore much deeper stretches in their traditional Yoga postures on the floor.    * Using an Aerial Yoga hammock can avoid common Yoga-related injuries such as over stretching the shoulders and too much compression in the lower back.

Michelle Dortignac has been a certified yoga instructor since 1998, and an aerial acrobatic performer since 2004. With an interest in helping her yoga students better understand proper alignment and the true purpose of yoga, she created the Unnata Aerial Yoga style in 2006, and continues to develop it today.Students use a Yoga hammock to dangle only inches off the ground. The hammock helps mold students' bodies into the shapes of traditional yoga postures through relaxation rather than muscular effort. This is what distinguishes Unnata Aerial Yoga from other fitness trends as well as from many other yoga techniques -- because gravity is already a strong force, students must learn to reduce the amount of effort they use. Once students have an idea of what the shape of the yoga posture is supposed to feel like, and which muscles they must relax in order for the shape to unfold, they have an easier time refinding that same posture on the floor, even without the assistance of the hammock",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/e6s3dO4BxebS7DY_sWo17Q/l.jpg,10

Sun 10:00 am - 3:00 pm & 5:30 pm - 9:15 pm","We offer classes in a vinyasa krama practice, also referred to as a vinyasa flow.  Our teachers come from eclectic backgrounds and offer insights from many different lineages and schools.  We recognize that Yoga comes from a colorful past. We welcome practitioners of all styles. Feel at home here to make your practice your own.We have structured our schedule to allow for a drop-in, pay-as-you-go experience.   We do not require sign-ups or registration. Yoga is an effective way to strengthen the body, calm the mind, and heighten the spirit, so we encourage everyone to practice as often as possible.Our studio was inspired by the teachings of Jules Febre and Rima Rani Rabbath of the international Jivamukti Yoga School.

Brahman Yoga was opened in May 2014, shortly after a team of scientists in Antarctica discovered evidence that the universe inflated into being faster than the speed of light.  Our universe, undoubtedly, is place of expansion.  Our studio was built to follow that example.  Yoga is a practice of opening our bodies, opening our minds, and opening our hearts.  It can be difficult to live in a universe of uncertainties.  Sometimes light travels as a particle, other times as a wave.  But when we demand answers and certainties, we usually find ourselves in conflict with the universe.  If, instead, we choose to expand our feelings and experiences, we might turn that conflict into a new connection.  Our studio's intention is to learn the importance of opening new space",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/d0KIEQJIUB1hMTaYL-DtMg/l.jpg,53

1574,Splash Fit Swimming,"14-32 W118th, New York, NY 10026",(917) 951-7057,NULL,splashfitswimming.com,"Mon Closed

Sun 2:00 pm - 5:00 pm","Swimming as FitnessThe benefits of cardiovascular activity and aerobic exercise are immense. According to the American Heart Association, physical activity will improve your overall quality of life. This notion is shared among most health institutions. Though learning how to swim is considered as a safety precaution for preventing a series of accidents when in or around water, swimming has been scientifically tested to improve one's well-being because it is part of a complete exercise regimen. It is considered to have the least amount of stress on joints with benefits like improved flexibility, strength, coordination, and aerobic prowess. Studies also show that the body becomes naturally inclined to consume more oxygen during high-intensity phases of exercise, which strengthens the lungs and allows swimmers to breathe at greater ease during rest. Aerobic exercise also decreases resting heart rate and blood pressure. The health benefits resulting of two to three 30 minute swim sessions each week can ultimately transform your lifestyle and drastically improve your overall well-being. You don't need to become an Olympic swimmer in order to enjoy the maximum benefits of aerobic exercises. However, you do need to challenge yourself. Here at Splash Fit Swimming, we encourage swimming to be used as a tool for great mental and physical health!

Splash Fit Swimming was founded by a group of aquatic instructors and coaches in Harlem teaching minority communities basic swimming skills and water safety awareness. With an epidemic of people drowning in the city, we wanted to expand our services where teaching a necessary life-saving skill has been our number one priority. We use advanced teaching techniques on levels based upon ability to promote learning. Our team adjusts the stroke curriculum to meet each swimmer's specific needs so that they can learn at their own pace, not only making sure that our clients are more comfortable around all aspects of aquatics, but ensuring that they develop a skill set that can be used for the rest of their lives. Our mission is to help participants reach their personal goals, whether it's for safety around water, staying healthy, competing at an elite level, or recreation",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/pVD_KCK4HDAMjirwCIypFA/l.jpg,3

Fri  & 5/29/2020 Closed","Welcome to Orangetheory Fitness, the energizing group interval fitness concept that is sweeping the nation! Orangetheory Fitness is a one-of-a-kind workout broken into intervals of cardiovascular and strength training, using a variety of equipment including treadmills, rowing, TRX straps, and free weights to tone your body and gain energy throughout the day.

The physiological theory behind the Orangetheory workout is known as Excess Post-Exercise Oxygen Consumption, or EPOC. By providing you with a heart rate monitor and POD, we can monitor your 5 zone interval training sessions that we call the Orange 60. During the 60 minute workout, you will perform multiple intervals designed to produce12 minutes or more of training at 84% or higher of your maximum heart rate, which translates to Zones 4/5. This program design produces EPOC, which is the workout after-burn effect, meaning that our interval training design produces a 200-400 calorie increase to your metabolism 24-36 hours after your workout",https://house-fastly.us-east-1.ooyala.com/RpcDNkajE6guNGOCOKeTqxpTa4J04IkR/Ut_HKthATH4eww8X4xMDoxOjBhOzV3Va,52

Sun 8:00 am - 4:00 pm","Balanced Pilates NYC is located in West Harlem and Lower East Side. Both studios are equipped with state-of-the-art Balanced Body equipment. Pilates is a mind/body exercise system originally created by Joseph H. Pilates in the 1920's. Pilates uses equipment such as the Reformer and Springboard to guide and control the movements promoting alignment and lengthening throughout the body. The best thing about Pilates is that it works for everyone. Whether you are an athlete or dancer looking to supplement your training, a senior combating osteoporosis or just trying to achieve longer, leaner muscle definition, Pilates is for you. Sitting for hours a day at a computer? Pilates will help you build the muscles and flexibility to sit taller and stronger with better posture. Recovering from an injury? Pilates can be a very effective rehabilitation tool. Are you Pre-Natal or Post-Natal? Pilates can help you stay in shape during your pregnancy and recover faster after. No matter your age or fitness level, Pilates can help you live a more balanced life.

Balanced Pilates opened its first West Harlem location in November of 2013.  In May of 2015, we are happy to announce the opening of our second location in Lower East Side",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/a-SffZGBvwWyhI2m4MDTjw/l.jpg,15

A significant landmark of New York City African-American culture, the Harlem YMCA is sometimes referred to as the living room of the Harlem Renaissance. Established in 1901, the Harlem YMCA has remained a cultural steward of Northern Manhattan and continues to serve the area's multicultural neighborhoods and communities with innovative programs and services that meet the unique needs of the individuals and families that call Harlem home.In 1971, financial consultant Dr. Leo B. Marsh initiated the Black Achievers program we know today: a volunteer adult mentoring model that helps youth to raise their academic standards and develop a positive sense of self. The program later expanded to support all teens of color.In April 2012, the Harlem Y won the prestigious American Dreamer Award in the Community Builder category from the NYC Mayor's Office of Immigrant Affairs (MOIA) for its work with immigrant New Yorkers through the Harlem YMCA New Americans Welcome Center",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/CiZ8YiI899j1bMJ2Viqhsg/l.jpg,34

1619,Crunch Fitness - Staten Island,"364 Bay St, Staten Island, NY 10301",(718) 816-7800,NULL,crunch.com,,"At Crunch Staten Island, there are no judgments. No too much or not enough. No glares of disapproval. Here, we keep open minds. We are nurturers, seeking only to encourage, empower, and entertain. We know that when it comes to fitness, there is no one type, no one reason, and no one way. We're a diverse community working together to create a culture of fun where there's room for everyone. No matter who you are, we're excited to help you reach your goals, and we just know that here in our clean, open space complete with real weights, tons of cardio, a Pilates studio, group fitness classes, world-class personal trainers, and more, you'll have no trouble doing just that.

Of all the great histories of all the great health clubs, Crunch's begins rather inauspiciously: in a basement level aerobics studio in New York City's East Village circa 1989. This, our first location, had no locker rooms, the air conditioning didn't work and after hours break-ins were perennial events. However, while we lacked the resources to equip the gym with some basic amenities and strong locks we were on an important mission - to make exercise fun. And, accomplishing this mission meant doing away with traditional notions of what a 'serious' workout should be. What we did was invite a highly creative group of fitness instructors with a wide range of expertise to collaborate with us. The result was the development of challenging programming with a completely fresh slant. Offerings like Hip-Hop Aerobics, Co-Ed Action Wrestling and Cyked Yoga Cycling were introduced and, along with others, became the embodiment of this new approach",https://secure-cf-c.ooyala.com/BtZTBoMzE6-7-rO4LzNiXBaphqnumP1p/Ut_HKthATH4eww8X4xMDoxOjBhOzV3Va,45
1620,Demarco's Boxing Gym,"140 Main St, Staten Island, NY 10309",(718) 227-2013,NULL,demarcosboxingclub.com,"Mon 9:00 am - 9:00 pm

Sun Closed","Nobody said training for the sport of boxing is easy! If it were, it wouldnt be effective. But, Demarcos Boxing Gym succeeds where traditional gyms fail, because we make training fun. When you enjoy what you are doing, reaching goals will always seem easier. The time, calories and stress of your day disappear, round-by-round. After an hour, you will leave physically exhausted but mentally refreshed.Forget running on a machine. Forget Simon-Says aerobics classes. Forget monotonous free-weights and machines. And forget the fashion-show drama of the franchise gyms where they have more mirrors than members. We will train your mind, your reflexes, and your muscles to be fit and fast. A trim physique and self-confidence are inevitable side effects of a balanced workout.

There is a stigma regarding boxing that we are doing our part to eliminate. Boxing is so much more than learning to hurt someone and it is nothing about the glamorization of violence. Sure, some of our members and many of our trainers have been in the ring on a competitive level, but these folks are exceptions to the rule in modern boxing facilities such as ours. AND, unless we told you who they were, you would never know. They are the nicest folks around and they truly love their sport. The majority of our members hold day jobs or go to school and do not come to the gym to be hit in the face! We have white-collar members, blue-collar members, teachers and homemakers among our ranks. We also train teenagers and children as young as 5 years old. We firmly believe that anyone can benefit from a boxing workout",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/51JHEIp9T6ksEgQLFWZ6Nw/l.jpg,6

Sun 11:00 am - 1:00 pm","Verrazano CrossFit in Staten Island, NY is a premier Crossfit facility to help you achieve all of your fitness goals. We work to inspire people to do their best every day. Verrazano Crossfit was launched at the conference room table of Coastal Plumbing Supply, a family owned business in the Stapleton section of Staten Island. It was founded on the idea that focusing on the health of our employee's would have a significant ripple effect on the entire company. Not only would the employee's life be enhanced, but so would the lives of those around them. As a result, our organization could create a strong and sustainable ROI in the form of an enhanced wellness culture and overall productivity, controlled health care and disability costs, sick time and turnover.Verrazano Crossfit is committed to helping other employers and customers in the community receive these same results. Utilizing Crossfit as a way to maximize the overall workplace experience and drive sales to the next level. Please feel free to contact us to learn more about the workplace wellness programs we are implementing throughout the NYC business community.We hope to see you soon at Verrazano CrossFit!

Sun Closed","Seido Karate is a traditional Japanese style of karate, into which its founder, Kaicho Tadashi Nakamura has distilled the essence of what he has learned about the martial arts in over 50 years of study, practice, and teaching.The World Seido Karate Organization officially opened its headquarters on October 15, 1976, in New York City. We are now a worldwide organization, with thriving branches throughout the United States and in such diverse places as Asia, Australia, Europe, New Zealand, South Africa, and South America. Nevertheless, within Seido, growth of our branch schools is not pursued for its own sake. Quality of instruction and development of the student is paramount.The physical training in Seido can be strenuous, emphasizing progressive development of strength, flexibility and aerobic capacity. In addition to developing students with the highest level of physical skill, Seido aims to develop individuals of the highest moral character.

The Staten Island Seido Karate dojo was founded by Jun-Shihan EdEllington in 1981. In 2007, upon his retirement from teaching, Kyoshi Roger Esposito was appointed Branch Chief Instructor for the Staten Island dojo. Kyoshi Roger and the other instructors have been instrumental in teaching students how to defend and protect oneself physically, while gaining confidence and self discipline, in order to meet the challenges of daily life. They instill the Seido Karate Bushido Spirit of facing challenges head on while always conducting oneself with respect, love and obedience",https://s3-media0.fl.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/6s9gGOysjlR31AyEDv10cw/l.jpg,3
